result.execSummary:
The defendant Inert Kenneth Gilles was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Copy of DE's DL and Driving Abstract given to the Court by DA at the June 8, 2016 Plea/Sentencing Hearing

Case called @ 3:15 p.m. Defendant Inert Kenneth Gilles in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: Ct 2 - NC.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Cts 1 & 3 - DRI. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Statement by DE regarding sentence. Court orders: S/W 1 year probation - Conditions: AODA and follow through, Abs Sob, DE is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician, Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal rights given.

Pre-trial conference on May 26, 2016 at 09:30 am.
Plea/sentencing hearing on June 8, 2016 at 03:45 pm.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

Case Called @ 2:42 PM: Defendant Inert Kenneth Gilles in court, appearing pro se.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def does not wish counsel today and wishes to speak with the State on resolution.   NGP entered by Court.   PTC and P/S Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for May 26, 2016 at 09:30 am.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for June 8, 2016 at 03:45 pm.
